verbose_text: Using a two-way between group ANOVA for histomorphometric analysis, a significant interaction revealed that disc height (XREF_FIG D), NP area (XREF_FIG E) and the number of NP cells (XREF_FIG F) was increased significantly in S3/S4 at all age points compared with P4 and this increase was significantly greater than in S1/S2 and S2/S3 levels.
